#. §2: `intro h`
#. §3: `7 < 5`
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L03_NonMembership
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L06_EmptySet
msgid "The goal is §0, which means §1. Use\n"
"§2 to assume §3."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L08_CompoundPredicate
msgid "6 belongs to the set of even naturals less than 10."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Set α`
#. §1: `α`
#. §2: `Set α`
#. §3: `α → Prop`
#. §4: `x : α`
#. §5: `s : Set α`
#. §6: `s x`
#. §7: `x ∈ s`
#. §8: `s x`
#. §9: `Set.ext`
#. §10: `Set α`
#. §11: `α`
#. §12: `Set.univ : Set α`
#. §13: `α`
#. §14: `Set α`
#. §15: `α`
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L01_WelcomeToSets
msgid "§0 is the type of sets with elements of type §1.\n"
"\n"
"In Lean, §2 is defined as §3 — a set IS its membership\n"
"predicate. An element §4 belongs to §5 when §6 is true.\n"
"\n"
"## Key facts\n"
"- Sets are predicates, not collections\n"
"- §7 means §8 (function application)\n"
"- Two sets are equal when they have the same elements (§9)\n"
"\n"
"## Warning\n"
"§10 is not the same as a type §11. A set is a *predicate on* a type.\n"
"§12 contains all elements of §13, but it is still a term\n"
"of type §14, not the type §15 itself."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Set.univ`
#. §1: `fun _ => True`
#. §2: `True`
#. §3: `constructor`
#. §4: `∅`
#. §5: `fun _ => False`
#. §6: `False`
#. §7: `∅ ⊆ s ⊆ Set.univ`
#. §8: `s : Set α`
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L07_UniversalSet
msgid "This is the universal counterpart of Level 1: instead of proving\n"
"membership for one element, you proved it for all elements.\n"
"\n"
"Compare the two *boundary sets*:\n"
"\n"
"| Set | Predicate | Membership | Proof |\n"
"|---|---|---|---|\n"
"| §0 | §1 | always §2 | §3 |\n"
"| §4 | §5 | always §6 | impossible |\n"
"\n"
"These two sets are the extreme cases. Every other set lies between\n"
"them: §7 for any §8. You will prove these\n"
"containments in the next world."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `{n : ℕ | n < 10 ∧ Even n}`
#. §1: $\\{0, 2, 4, 6, 8\\}$
#. §2: `6 ∈ {n | n < 10 ∧ Even n}`
#. §3: `6 < 10 ∧ Even 6`
#. §4: `constructor`
#. §5: `constructor`
#. §6: `6 < 10 ∧ Even 6`
#. §7: `6 < 10`
#. §8: `omega`
#. §9: `Even 6`
#. §10: `3`
#. §11: `6 = 3 + 3`
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L08_CompoundPredicate
msgid "# Compound Predicates\n"
"\n"
"So far, each set predicate has tested a single condition. But predicates\n"
"can combine conditions using logical connectives.\n"
"\n"
"The set §0 contains even numbers less than 10:\n"
"the set §1.\n"
"\n"
"Membership unfolds to the conjunction: §2\n"
"becomes §3. To prove a conjunction, you split it with\n"
"§4 and prove each part separately.\n"
"\n"
"The proof strategy:\n"
"1. §5 — split §6 into two goals\n"
"2. Prove §7 with §8\n"
"3. Prove §9 by providing the witness §10 (since §11)\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that 6 belongs to the set of even numbers less than 10."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `trivial`
#. §1: `rfl`
#. §2: `exact True.intro`
#. §3: `assumption`
#: Game.Metadata
msgid "§0 attempts to close the goal using a combination of\n"
"basic tactics (§1, §2, §3).\n"
"\n"
"Disabled because it bypasses the learning of specific proof steps."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.SetWorld
msgid "Set World"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `exact e`
#. §1: `e`
#. §2: ```
#. exact expression
#. ```
#: Game.Metadata
msgid "§0 closes the goal if §1 has exactly the type of the goal.\n"
"\n"
"## Syntax\n"
"§2\n"
"\n"
"## When to use it\n"
"When you have a term (variable, function application, constructor)\n"
"whose type matches the goal exactly."
msgstr ""

