#. §14: `→ False`
#. §15: `∀ x, P x`
#. §16: `P → Q`
#. §17: `intro`
#. §18: `h : False`
#. §19: `exact h`
#. §20: `False`
#. §21: `False`
#. §22: `0 = 1`
#. §23: `exact h`
#. §24: `False`
#. §25: `Set.univ`
#. §26: `fun _ => True`
#. §27: `∅`
#. §28: `fun _ => False`
#: Game.Levels.SetWorld.L06_EmptySet
msgid "The empty set §0 is defined by the predicate §1, so\n"
"membership always reduces to §2.\n"
"\n"
"The proof pattern:\n"
"- §3 means §4\n"
"- After §5 and §6, the hypothesis §7 has type §8\n"
"  (because §9 IS §10)\n"
"- §11 closes the goal\n"
"\n"
"Notice that §12 handled TWO different things here: first a universal\n"
"quantifier (§13), then an implication (§14). Both work because\n"
"under the Curry-Howard correspondence, §15 and §16 are\n"
"both function types — §17 is the same operation in both cases.\n"
"\n"
"Also note the *ex falso* principle at work: if you have §18,\n"
"then §19 closes ANY goal, not just §20. Here the goal\n"
"happened to be §21, but if it were §22 or anything else,\n"
"§23 would still work. §24 implies everything — this is\n"
"*ex falso quodlibet* (from falsehood, anything follows).\n"
"\n"
"Compare with Level 1: there, §25 had predicate §26,\n"
"so membership was trivially provable. Here, §27 has predicate\n"
"§28, so membership is impossible. The two sets are\n"
"mirror images."
msgstr ""

